<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-21T14:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-21T14:41:00-05:00" n="845" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6302.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Saltillo</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Saltillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-21T13:00:00-06:41">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1913—1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Governor Carranza has officially announced to me that he will conform
                            with the new administration at Mexico City. All opposition here
                            abandoned. Railroads will be opened at once. Perfect quiet prevails.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Holland</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>